Japan’s Bonds Fall, Send 10-Year Yield to 1%, as Nikkei Rallies

-- B y   M a s a k i   K o n d o
-- 
2011-09-27T06:20:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/japan-s-bonds-fall-send-10-year-yield-to-1-as-nikkei-rallies.html
Japan ’s bonds fell, sending yields
on 10-year securities up 2.5 basis points to 1 percent, as gains
in domestic shares curbed demand for government debt.  The yield on the 20-year bond increased three basis points
to 1.71 percent as of 3:15 p.m. in  Tokyo . The Nikkei 225 Stock
Average surged 2.8 percent, climbing from a two-year low.  To contact the reporter on this story:
